    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5155854>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. — Chimarra antsymeloka n. sp., abdominal segments VIII, IX and X (without inferior appendages and phallic apparatus), caudal view. Abbreviations: ldl, latero-dorsal lobe; lvl, latero-ventral lobe; s, segment; t, tergum; vp, ventral process. Scale bar: 0.1 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5155854/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5155860>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. — A-C, wings: A, Chimarra vulgaris n. sp.; B, Chimarra antsymeloka n. sp.; C, Chimarra assambae n. sp. Scale bar: 1 mm. Abbreviations: A, anal vein; Cu, cubitus; M, medius; R, radius; Sc, subcosta." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5155860/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5155863>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. — A, B, Chimarra callasae Gibon,1982:A, segments IX and X,lateral view; B, phallic apparatus,lateral view;C, D, Chimarra minima Ulmer, 1907, holotype male: C, segments IX and X, lateral view; D, phallic apparatus, lateral view; E, Chimarra sassandrae Gibon, 1982, segments IX and X, lateral view; F, Chimarra toubaensis Gibon, 1985, segments IX and X, lateral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5155863/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5155872>
    dc:description "FIG. 5. — A-F, Chimarra antsymeloka n. sp.: A, inferior appendage, dorsal view; B, segments IX and X, lateral view; C, tergum X, dorsal view; D, Chimarra antsymeloka n. sp., specimen from the Efaho River (near Ifarantsa), tergum X, dorsal view; E, Chimarra antsymeloka n. sp., specimen from the Menarandra River (near Tranoroa), tergum X, dorsal view; F, phallic apparatus, lateral view; G, Chimarra ambaja Mosely, 1939, segments IX and X, lateral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5155872/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

